detaileddescription.para: Copies len bytes from the buffer src to the buffer dest. Behaviour is undefined if the memory regions overlap.
Copies n bytes from the buffer src to the buffer dest. Unlike memcpy(), handles overlapping regions safely.
Compares n bytes of the buffers s1 and s2.

simplesect.para: An integer less than, equal to, or greater than zero if the first differing byte in s1 is found to be less than, equal to, or greater than the corresponding byte in s2. Returns zero if all compared bytes are equal.

briefdescription.para: Fill a block of memory with a constant value.

detaileddescription.para: Sets the first len bytes of the buffer dest to the value val.

briefdescription.para: Reverse a block of memory in place.

detaileddescription.para: Reverses the order of n bytes in the buffer buf.

parameterdescription.para: Pointer to the buffer to reverse.

simplesect.para: Number of bytes reversed (same as n).

detaileddescription.para: Provides standard routines for copying, moving, comparing, setting, and reversing blocks of memory. These are implemented as part of the kernel runtime and are not dependent on libc.
